==English==
===Etymology===
A particularly vicious fight between cats or other animals is one that sends fur flying.
===Adjective===
'''fur-flying'''
# [[vicious]]
===Quotations===
*'''2006''': 'Anticlimactic as it may have been, the news last week that Meredith Vieira would replace Katie Couric on the “Today” show marked the dénouement of a '''fur-flying''', nail-biting, years-long game of musical chairs among television’s leading ladies.' &mdash; ''The New Yorker,'' 17 April 2006, page 27.